{
  "text": "Contrary to our study, Kundra et al. [CITATION_1] reported a progressive increase in heart rate in all of their patients, although the increase was significantly greater in the nebulization group than in the combined regional block group. The mean arterial pressure of their nebulization group was also higher than that of the combined regional block group. In our study, dexmedetomidine (1 μg/kg, IV) before the procedure was effective in producing good sedation and analgesia, without marked alteration of hemodynamic parameters.",
